# Permissions

CSA Admin uses a permission system to control what each admin can see and do. Every admin is assigned a permission that determines their access level across all features of the application.

## Access Levels {#access-levels}

Each feature has two possible access levels:

- **Read** – The admin can view all data related to the feature but cannot create, edit, or delete anything.
- **Write** – Full access: the admin can create, edit, delete, and perform all actions related to the feature (validate members, send invoices, cancel memberships, etc.).

By default, when no explicit right is set for a feature, an admin has **read** access to it. This means every admin can always see everything; permissions only control who can make changes.

## Super Admin {#super-admin}

The Super Admin permission is created automatically and cannot be edited or deleted. Admins with this permission have **write** access to every feature, including sensitive ones that are reserved for Super Admins only (see [reserved features](#reserved-features) below).

This is the permission to assign to organization managers and people who need full control over settings, deliveries, and the admin team.

## Custom Permissions {#custom-permissions}

You can [create custom permissions](/permissions/new) to tailor access for different roles in your team. For each feature, choose between read and write access. For example, you could create:

- A **"Billing manager"** permission with write access only to billing.
- A **"Delivery coordinator"** permission with write access to deliveries, depots, and members.
- A **"Newsletter editor"** permission with write access only to newsletters.

To create a permission, go to [Admins](/admins) > [Permissions](/permissions) > "New permission".

> A custom permission can only be deleted if no admins are currently assigned to it.

## Reserved Features {#reserved-features}

Some features are reserved for the Super Admin and are always **read-only** for custom permissions. These are features where changes affect the entire organization:

| Feature | What it controls |
|---------|-----------------|
| Admins | Creating and managing admin accounts |
| <%= BasketSize.model_name.human(count: 2) %> | Creating and configuring <%= BasketSize.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> |
| <%= BasketComplement.model_name.human(count: 2) %> | Creating and configuring <%= BasketComplement.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> |
| Deliveries | Creating and managing delivery dates and [delivery cycles](/handbook/deliveries#delivery-cycles) |
| Permissions | Creating and managing permissions |
| Email templates | Editing [automatic email templates](/handbook/mail_templates) |

## Configurable Features {#configurable-features}

These features can be set to read or write independently on each custom permission:

| Feature | What it controls |
|---------|-----------------|
| Members | Managing member profiles, validating registrations, changing statuses |
| Memberships | Creating, editing, and renewing memberships |
| Billing | Managing invoices, payments, and billing operations |
| Depots | Managing depots and depot groups |
| Announcements | Creating [announcements](/handbook/announcements) on delivery sheets |
| Newsletters | Creating and sending [newsletters](/handbook/newsletters) |

Additionally, any [optional feature](/settings#organization_features_input) enabled for your organization (absences, activities, shop, etc.) also appears in the list and can be configured per permission.

## Notification Preferences {#notifications}

Independently from permissions, each admin can subscribe to email notifications for specific events. These are configured from each admin's [profile page](/admins), not from the permission itself.

Available notifications include:

- **New registration** – when a member registers through the form
- **Delivery list** – when a delivery list is ready
- **New email suppression** – when an email bounces or is suppressed
- **Trial cancellation** – when a member cancels during their trial period
- **Invoice overpaid** – when a payment exceeds the invoice amount
- **3rd overdue notice** – when an invoice reaches its third reminder
- **Payment reversal** – when a payment is reversed

Additional notifications are available depending on your enabled features (new absence, new activity participation, etc.).

> Each admin manages their own notifications. Permissions do not affect which notifications an admin can subscribe to.
